  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Jamieson-Fausset-Brown Bible Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "22. Moreover thou gavest them kingdoms and nations—that is, put them in possession of a rich country, of an extensive territory, which had been once occupied by a variety of princes and people.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and didst divide them into corners—that is, into tribes. The propriety of the expression arose from the various districts touching at points or angles on each other.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "the land of Sihon, and the land of the king of Heshbon—Heshbon being the capital city, the passage should run thus: \"the land of Sihon or the land of the king of Heshbon.\"",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
