  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And testifiedst against them,.... By sending prophets to them, to admonish them of their sins, and remind them of their duty: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "that thou mightest bring them again unto thy law; to regard it, and walk according it: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "yet they dealt proudly; with an haughty air rejected the counsel of God: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and hearkened not unto thy commandments; yielded not obedience to them: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "but sinned against thy judgments; transgressed his laws, which were so just, righteous, reasonable, and equitable: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "which if a man do, he shall live in them; or by them, in the land of Canaan, see Leviticus 18:5, ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "which if a man do, he shall live in them; or by them, in the land of Canaan, see ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Leviticus 18:5",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ", ",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and withdrew the shoulder, and hardened their neck, and would not hear; like oxen, that wriggle and struggle, and draw back, and will not admit the yoke upon them. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "and withdrew the shoulder, and hardened their neck, and would not hear; like oxen, that wriggle and struggle, and draw back, and will not admit the yoke upon them. ",
