            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". On the figurative expression, they gave a resisting shoulder, comp. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Zechariah 7:11",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". The simile is taken from the ox, who rears against the yoke, and desires not to bear it; comp. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Hosea 4:16",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". The sentences following are repeated from ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Nehemiah 9:16",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". עליהם תּמשׁך is an abbreviated expression for חסד משׁך, ",
